# Carnatic Guru-Shishya Knowledge Graph — Roo Session Rules

**[2026-04-16] MIGRATION NOTE**: Agent personas and workflows are now defined in `CLAUDE.md` (at project root).
This file (`.clinerules`) contains workflows, CLI tools, data model reference, and learning logs — the operating manual.
See CLAUDE.md for agent boundaries and system overview.

## Project layout
```
carnatic/
  data/musicians.json     ← canonical source of truth (nodes + edges + recordings)
  data/compositions.json  ← ragas[], composers[], compositions[] — bani flow seed data
  render/                 ← render package; entry point: `bani-render` (or `.venv/bin/bani-render`)
  crawl.py                ← Wikipedia scraper (uses disk cache in data/cache/)
  serve.py                ← zero-dep local server, opens http://localhost:8765/graph.html
  graph.html              ← derived artefact — NEVER hand-edit
```


## Virtual environment — HARD RULE

All commands in this project must run inside the project `.venv`:
```bash
source .venv/bin/activate   # once per shell session
# then:
bani-render               # rebuild graph.html
bani-serve                # local dev server
python3 carnatic/cli.py stats
```
If `.venv` is not activated, `bani-render` will not be found on PATH.
Never use the system `python3` or a global `pip` for this project.

## Agent domain boundaries — HARD RULES

| Agent | May edit | Must never edit |
|---|---|---|
| 📚 Librarian | `*.json` data files only | `.py`, `.html`, `.js` code files |
| 🎵 Carnatic Coder | `.py`, `.html`, `.js`, `.md`, `.sh`, `.css` | Any `.json` file directly |
| 🏛️ Graph Architect | `plans/*.md` ADRs | Data files, code files |

**The Carnatic Coder must never directly edit or create any `.json` file.** If a JSON file needs changing, the Coder writes a script; the Librarian reviews and applies it.

## Session startup
0. **Activate the project venv first:** `source .venv/bin/activate` — all `bani-*` commands and `python3 carnatic/` scripts must run inside this venv.
1. **Read CLAUDE.md** at the project root — it defines the 4-agent system (Librarian, Coder, Architect, Orchestrator) and agent boundaries.
2. Run `python3 carnatic/cli.py stats` to orient — replaces reading `musicians.json` and `compositions.json` in full.
3. Use targeted CLI queries (see **CLI Tools** section below) before any `read_file` call.
4. Read the **Open questions** section below — it is the living memory of this project.
5. At the end of every session: update the Open questions section, append your learning log entry (see **Agent learning logs** section below), then **commit and push your work** (see Git protocol below).

> **Full file reads** (`read_file: musicians.json`) are reserved for patching sessions where you need to construct an `apply_diff` block. Even then, use `python3 carnatic/cli.py get-musician <id>` to retrieve the exact current value of a field before constructing the diff — not the whole file. For the canonical data schema, see `carnatic/data/READYOU.md`.

## CLI Tools (ADR-014)
```bash
# Orientation
python3 carnatic/cli.py stats

# Existence checks (exit 0 = found, exit 1 = not found)
python3 carnatic/cli.py musician-exists   <id_or_label>
python3 carnatic/cli.py raga-exists       <id_or_name>
python3 carnatic/cli.py composition-exists <id_or_title>
python3 carnatic/cli.py recording-exists  <id_or_title>
python3 carnatic/cli.py url-exists        <youtube_url>

# Lookup (compact summary; add --json for full object)
python3 carnatic/cli.py get-musician      <id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py get-raga          <id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py get-composition   <id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py gurus-of          <musician_id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py shishyas-of       <musician_id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py lineage           <musician_id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py recordings-for    <musician_id>
python3 carnatic/cli.py compositions-in-raga <raga_id>

# Validation (run after any write or apply_diff patch)
python3 carnatic/cli.py validate
```

## Write CLI Tools (ADR-015)

**Use these commands for all standard write operations.** They are atomic, validate
referential integrity before writing, and are idempotent (safe to run twice).
`write_cli.py` writes only to `musicians.json` and `compositions.json` — never to
`graph.json` (a derived artefact). After any write session, run `bani-render`.

```bash
# Musician graph writes
python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-musician     --id <id> --label <label> --era <era> \
                                                --instrument <inst> --source-url <url> \
                                                --source-label <label> --source-type <type> \
                                                [--born <year>] [--died <year>] [--bani <bani>]

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-edge         --source <guru_id> --target <shishya_id> \
                                                --confidence <float> --source-url <url> \
                                                [--note <text>]

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-youtube      --musician-id <id> --url <yt_url> \
                                                --label <label> \
                                                [--composition-id <id>] [--raga-id <id>] \
                                                [--year <int>] [--version <text>]

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-source       --musician-id <id> --url <url> \
                                                --label <label> --type <type>

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py remove-edge      --source <guru_id> --target <shishya_id>

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py patch-musician   --id <id> --field <field> --value <value>
# Permitted fields: label, born, died, era, instrument, bani  (id is immutable)

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py patch-edge       --source <guru_id> --target <shishya_id> \
                                                --field <field> --value <value>
# Permitted fields: confidence, source_url, note

# Composition data writes
python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-raga         --id <id> --name <name> \
                                                --source-url <url> --source-label <label> \
                                                --source-type <type> \
                                                [--aliases <csv>] [--melakarta <int>] \
                                                [--parent-raga <id>] [--notes <text>]

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-composer     --id <id> --name <name> \
                                                --source-url <url> --source-label <label> \
                                                --source-type <type> \
                                                [--musician-node-id <id>] \
                                                [--born <year>] [--died <year>]

python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-composition  --id <id> --title <title> \
                                                --composer-id <id> --raga-id <id> \
                                                [--tala <tala>] [--language <lang>] \
                                                [--source-url <url>] [--source-label <label>] \
                                                [--source-type <type>] [--notes <text>]
```

**Exit codes:** 0 = written or duplicate-skipped. 1 = validation error (file unchanged).
**Output prefixes:** `[NODE+]` `[EDGE+]` `[EDGE-]` `[EDGE~]` `[YOUTUBE+]` `[RAGA+]` `[COMPOSER+]` `[COMP+]` `[SOURCE+]` `SKIP (duplicate)` `ERROR`

> **When to use `apply_diff` instead:** Recording files (`recordings/*.json`), adding
> `notes` fields to compositions, or any operation not yet covered by `write_cli.py`.

### YouTube ingestion — mandatory pre-checks (Workflow A + H)
Before adding any YouTube link:
1. `python3 carnatic/cli.py url-exists <url>` — if FOUND, report and stop.
2. `python3 carnatic/cli.py musician-exists "<artist name>"` — note exact id if FOUND; flag if NOT FOUND.
3. `python3 carnatic/cli.py raga-exists "<raga name>"` — note exact id if FOUND; add raga first (`add-raga`) if NOT FOUND, then `bani-render`.
4. `python3 carnatic/cli.py composition-exists "<composition name>"` — note exact id if FOUND; add composition first (`add-composition`) if NOT FOUND, then `bani-render`.
5. `python3 carnatic/write_cli.py add-youtube --musician-id <id> --url <url> --label <label> [--raga-id <id>] [--composition-id <id>] [--year <year>]`

### Playlist ingestion (Workflow H — batch from playlist_meta.py output)
```
Step 0: bani-render  (ensure graph.json is current)
Step 1: For each playlist entry — run pre-checks 1–4 above, then add-youtube.
Step 2: bani-render && python3 carnatic/cli.py validate
```

## Core workflow
1. User drops a Wikipedia URL, YouTube link+title, or verbal correction
2. **Use `write_cli.py` commands** for standard mutations; fall back to `apply_diff` only for operations not covered
3. When tagging recordings: also add `composition_id`, `raga_id`, `year` to youtube entries where identifiable
4. Run `bani-render` — confirm node/edge counts change as expected
5. Run `python3 carnatic/serve.py` to visualise (or remind user to refresh if already running)
6. **End of session**: update Open questions below, then **commit and push** — include a plain-prose summary of what changed in the commit body.

## Patching rules
- **Never edit `graph.html` by hand**
- **Prefer `write_cli.py` commands** over hand-constructed `apply_diff` blocks for all covered operations
- `apply_diff` remains valid for recording files and uncovered operations
- Log every change: `[NODE+]`, `[EDGE+]`, `[EDGE-]`, `[EDGE~]`
- Check for duplicate `id` (nodes) and `(source, target)` pair (edges) before appending

## Adding a musician
1. Fetch Wikipedia page; extract infobox `teacher`/`students` + prose lineage patterns
2. Check all existing `label` fields for name variant collisions before creating a node
3. Significance filter: Sangeetha Kalanidhi recipient, or necessary topological link
4. Use `note` to qualify: `"first guru"`, `"principal guru"`, `"gurukula training, N years"`
5. **Do not infer edges from shared bani** — require explicit lineage statement

## Wikipedia URL health — optional audit
Run this at the start of a session (or on request) to surface broken links for human attention.
The agent **reports** broken URLs; it does **not** automatically hunt replacements unless asked.
```bash
python3 -c "
import urllib.request, json, time
with open('carnatic/data/musicians.json') as f: data = json.load(f)
for node in data['nodes']:
    url = node['wikipedia']
    try:
        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})
        resp = urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=8)
        final = resp.geturl()
        status = 'REDIRECT → ' + final if final != url else 'OK'
    except Exception as e:
        status = '404'
    if status != 'OK':
        print(f\"{status:40s}  {node['id']}  {url}\")
    time.sleep(0.25)
"
```
- **404** lines = stub or wrong title; flag in Open questions below for community attention
- **REDIRECT** lines = URL works but should be updated to the canonical final URL
- Nodes with no own Wikipedia page are valid; their `wikipedia` field should point to the
  page that most prominently mentions them (e.g. a parent's article)

## Adding YouTube recordings
- Links **must be annotated** with the video title (URL alone is not enough)
- Parse title → identify artist(s) → match to existing node `label`
- Extract 11-char video ID; append extended object to node's `youtube` array
- A recording can belong to multiple nodes (duets etc.)
- Flag unmatched artists — do not silently drop or create unevaluated nodes
- **Always tag** `composition_id`, `raga_id`, and `year` where identifiable from the title/metadata
- `composition_id` and `raga_id` must reference IDs in `compositions.json`; add new entries there first if needed

## Adding compositions/ragas
- New ragas: add to `compositions.json` `ragas[]` — require Wikipedia URL and musicological `notes`
- New composers: add to `compositions.json` `composers[]` — set `musician_node_id` if they are also a lineage node
- New compositions: add to `compositions.json` `compositions[]` — require verified `composer_id` and `raga_id`
- IDs are snake_case and permanent once set — never rename
- After any change to `compositions.json`, re-run `bani-render` to rebuild lookup tables

## Data model quick reference
**Node:** `id` (snake_case, never rename), `label`, `wikipedia`, `born`, `died`, `era`, `instrument`, `bani`, `youtube[]`
**Edge:** `source` (guru id), `target` (shishya id), `confidence` (0–1), `source_url`, `note`
**YouTube entry (extended):** `url`, `label`, `composition_id` (opt), `raga_id` (opt), `year` (opt)
**Era values:** `trinity` · `bridge` · `golden_age` · `disseminator` · `living_pillars` · `contemporary`
**Instrument values:** `vocal` · `veena` · `violin` · `flute` · `mridangam` · `bharatanatyam` (add new freely)
**Confidence:** 0.95–1.0 explicit · 0.85–0.94 cross-confirmed · 0.70–0.84 single source · <0.70 speculative (must have `note`)
**compositions.json raga:** `id`, `name`, `aliases`, `melakarta`, `parent_raga`, `wikipedia`, `notes`
**compositions.json composer:** `id`, `name`, `musician_node_id`, `born`, `died`, `wikipedia`
**compositions.json composition:** `id`, `title`, `composer_id`, `raga_id`, `tala`, `language`, `wikipedia`, `notes`

## Change log prefixes
`[NODE+]` · `[EDGE+]` · `[EDGE-]` · `[EDGE~]` · `[YOUTUBE+]` · `[YOUTUBE~]` · `[COMP+]` · `[RAGA+]` · `[COMPOSER+]` · `[FLAG]`

## Server
```bash
python3 carnatic/serve.py        # http://localhost:8765/graph.html
python3 carnatic/serve.py 9000   # custom port
```
YouTube embeds require localhost — never open graph.html as a file:// URL.

