- 2026-05-10: ADR-122 backfill: `melakarta_new.json` has 59 entries (legacy snapshot) but the authoritative source is `carnatic/data/ragas/*.json` which already had all 72 melakarta present after ADR-021 Phase 3 work — always count from the ragas/ dir, not from melakarta_new.json; the two files are out of sync.
- 2026-05-10: The katapayadi formula `katapayadi_from_mela(M)` uniquely determines the swara tuple for every mela — it is the single source of truth; the derivation is: madhyama=1 if M≤36 else 2; within-hemisphere n=M or M-36; cakra_idx=(n-1)//6 → (ri,ga) upper-triangular pair; pos_in_cakra=(n-1)%6 → (da,ni) upper-triangular pair; validated by round-trip for all 72.
- 2026-05-10: `PATCHABLE_RAGA_FIELDS` in writer.py gates which fields `patch_raga` accepts; adding `katapayadi` to that set is the correct minimal diff to support dict-valued raga fields written programmatically; the caller passes the dict directly and no CLI string-coercion branch is needed.
- 2026-05-10: The ADR-122 validation block in `cli.py validate` uses `g.get_all_ragas()` (reads from graph.json) so `bani-render` must run before validate reflects the backfill — this is the standard render gate; add the ADR-122 check line to the `checks[]` list at the bottom of cmd_validate so the success message names the new invariant.
- 2026-05-10: ADR-123 wheel: `_collapseAll` queried `circle[data-mela]` — changing mela nodes from `<circle>` to `<path>` requires updating all such selectors to `path[data-mela]`; always grep the full JS file for element-type-prefixed attribute selectors before switching a node's SVG element type.
- 2026-05-10: ADR-123 wheel: `melaAngles[i] = (i+0.5) * 2π/72` centres each angle in its 5° arc slot — using `i * 2π/72` (the old circle-node convention) misaligns janya fan anchor angles by half a slot; shift to centred angles when migrating from point nodes to arc sectors.
- 2026-05-10: ADR-123 ring radii are a strict monotone sequence (R_MADHYAMA 0.10 → R_CAKRA 0.18 → R_RIGA 0.26 → R_DANI 0.34 → R_MELA 0.42 → R_LABEL 0.50 → R_JANYA 0.62 → R_COMP 0.78 → R_MUSC 0.92); assert this ordering in any script that reads or modifies these constants.
