- 2026-06-10: AUDIT-015: both reported Plyr bugs trace to the single `new Plyr` site in `mountPlayer` (media_player.js:783), the only Plyr config in the repo, shared by desktop (createPlayer:851) and mobile (_openMobilePlayer:3289). Mute double-click = `autoplay:true` with no `muted` → browser starts YouTube muted (muted autoplay always allowed, unmuted needs a fresh gesture lost across async iframe-ready), and Plyr's mute icon renders from its own config not the engine state, so the icon lies; canonical fix is `muted:true` then unmute on first `playing` event so the UI tracks reality (one click, not two). Click-to-pause failure = `clickToPlay` defaults true but the cross-origin YouTube iframe eats the centre click; `play-large` shows a central button only in paused state, making the body look interactive when it is not — fix is a transparent overlay above the iframe and below the control bar calling `player.togglePlay()`. Watch that `controller.onTime`/`onEnded` (ADR-156/157) stay wired after any mount change.
[AGENTS: code-auditor]
- 2026-06-10: AUDIT-015 fix implemented in mountPlayer: added `muted:true` + `player.once('playing', () => player.muted = false)` — unmuting an already-*playing* video is allowed without a fresh gesture, so sound now lands on first open with zero clicks (better than the audit's two-click conservative framing). For click-to-pause, set `clickToPlay: !isEmbed` (HTML5 keeps Plyr's native handler; embeds turn it off to avoid a double-toggle) and append a `.mp-click-catch` div to `player.elements.wrapper` on `ready` for youtube/vimeo only. Z-index is the crux: catcher at `z-index:1` sits above the iframe (z0) but below play-large (z2) and the control bar (z3, also `pointer-events:none` until hover) — `.plyr__video-wrapper` has position:relative but NO z-index so it creates no stacking context and the catcher's z1 compares directly against the controls' z3 in the `.plyr` context. CSS rule lives beside the ADR-155 `.mp-has-plyr .plyr` block in base.html.
[AGENTS: carnatic-coder]
